The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

                                        Archives
                                                                                                                                    The City Diary

        nA group of four armed men slashed the throat of 45-year-old trader Anil Ranjan Pal in Birati on Thursday night. Pal, who owns a jewellery shop in Bowbazar, was returning home when the group stopped his motorcycle and robbed him. When Pal raised an alarm, the group attacked him, hit him with a revolver butt and fled the spot. Pal was shifted to a local hospital, where his condition was said to be critical.
  nSix armed men looted Rs 50,000 from a government office in Baruipur, on southern fringes of the city, early on Friday after assaulting the guard. Police said the gang entered the building and tied up guard Gobinda Mondal to a pillar and gagged him with a piece of cloth. Before leaving, the dacoits burst a bomb. The police suspect one of them was injured, because the room had blood stains.
  nHomemaker Pinki Mudili, 22, committed suicide by hanging herself from the ceiling of her Beniapukur residence late on Thursday. She was declared dead when taken to National Medical College and Hospital. No suicide note was found. Police are interrogating her husband and in-laws.
                                                                             
